'''Salih Özcan''' (born 11 January 1998) is a professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|salih-oezcan}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Köln===
Born in Germany, Özcan is of Turkish descent as he was born into a Turkish family. Özcan spent the majority of his youth career in [[1. FC Köln]]'s youth system. He first featured in 1. FC Köln's first team in September 2016 in a [[Bundesliga]] match against [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fc.de/fc-info/news/detailseite/details/drei-punkte-auf-schalke/ |title=Drei Punkte auf Schalke |website=1.FC Köln |language=de |access-date=24 May 2018 |archive-date=5 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230405233513/https://fc.de/fc-info/news/detailseite/details/drei-punkte-auf-schalke/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> During the [[2017–18 Bundesliga|2017–18 season]] he consistently started in central midfield. He scored his first league goal on 2 September 2018 in a [[2. Bundesliga]] match against [[FC St. Pauli]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ndr.de/sport/fussball/St-Pauli-verliert-Torspektakel-gegen-Koeln,pauli5392.html |title=St. Pauli verliert Torspektakel gegen Köln |website=NDR.de |language=de |access-date=2 September 2018 }}{{Dead link|date=August 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

In 2017, Özcan was awarded the golden [[Fritz Walter Medal]] for the best U19 player in Germany.<ref name="FWA">{{cite web|url=https://www.ksta.de/sport/1-fc-koeln/auszeichnung-vor-laenderspiel-fc-talent-oeczan-mit-fritz-walter-medaille-ausgezeichnet-28359238 |title=Auszeichnung vor Länderspiel FC-Talent: Öczan mit Fritz-Walter-Medaille ausgezeichnet |website=Kölner Stadtanzeiger |date=5 September 2017 |language=de |access-date=24 May 2018 }}</ref>

====Loan to Holstein Kiel====
[[File:SalihÖzcan.jpg|thumb|Özcan at [[Holstein Kiel]] in 2019]]
On 23 August 2019, Özcan joined [[Holstein Kiel]] on loan until the end of 2019–20 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.holstein-kiel.de/allgemein/die-ksv-verpflichtet-salih-oezcan-vom-1-fc-koeln/|title=Die KSV verpflichtet Özcan vom 1. FC Köln|publisher=Holstein Kiel|language=German|date=23 August 2019|accessdate=23 August 2019|archive-date=23 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823213408/https://www.holstein-kiel.de/allgemein/die-ksv-verpflichtet-salih-oezcan-vom-1-fc-koeln/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Three days later, he made his debut with the team as a starter in a [[2. Bundesliga]] away match against [[FC St. Pauli]], which ended in a 2–1 defeat.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/548637/holstein-kiel-st-pauli |title=St. Pauli 2–1 Holstein Kiel |publisher=ESPN |date=26 August 2019 }}</ref>

====Return to Köln====
[[File:2021-08-08 FC Carl Zeiss Jena gegen 1. FC Köln (DFB-Pokal) by Sandro Halank–154.jpg|thumb|Özcan playing for [[1. FC Köln]] in 2021]]
On 29 June 2021, in spite of speculations about a possible transfer, the club announced that Özcan had signed a new two-year contract with Köln.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fc.de/fc-info/news/detailseite/details/fc-verlaengert-mit-salih-oezcan/|title=FC verlängert mit Salih Özcan|access-date=2021-06-29|website=[[1. FC Köln]]|language=de|archive-date=19 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719051553/https://fc.de/fc-info/news/detailseite/details/fc-verlaengert-mit-salih-oezcan/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Borussia Dortmund===
On 23 May 2022, it was reported that Özcan would join [[Borussia Dortmund]] for the [[2022–23 Bundesliga|2022–23 season]] and that he would sign a contract with the club until 2026. The German sports magazine ''[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]]'' estimated the transfer fee to be €5 million.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/vierter-bvb-neuzugang-perfekt-oezcan-kommt-vom-1-fc-koeln-902841/artikel |title=Vierter BVB-Neuzugang perfekt: Özcan kommt vom 1. FC Köln |website=kicker |language=de}}</ref>

On 27 August 2022, he made his debut with the team as a starter in a [[Bundesliga]] match against [[Hertha BSC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/hertha-bsc-vs-dortmund/spielbericht/465788 |title=Hertha BSC - BVB: Borussia Dortmund gewinnt in Berlin |publisher=Sky Sport |language=de |date=27 August 2022 }}</ref> On 6 September 2022, he made his continental debut with the team in a [[UEFA Champions League]] match against [[F.C. Copenhagen|København]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/652587/fc-k%C3%B8benhavn-borussia-dortmund |title=Borussia Dortmund 3–0 F.C. København |publisher=ESPN |date=6 September 2022 }}</ref>

====Loan to Wolfsburg====
On 28 August 2024, Özcan moved on loan to [[VfL Wolfsburg]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=VfL Wolfsburg|url=https://www.vfl-wolfsburg.de/newsdetails/news-detail/detail/news/leihe-vom-bvb|title=Leihe vom BVB|trans-title=Loan from BVB|date=28 August 2024|access-date=28 August 2024|language=de}}</ref> Three days later, he made his debut with Wolfsburg in a 2–0 away win against his former club Holstein Kiel.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfl-wolfsburg.de/en/newsdetails/news-detail/detail/news/comfortable-away-win-2-1 |title=Comfortable away win |publisher=VfL Wolfsburg |date=31 August 2024 }}</ref>

====Return to Borussia Dortmund====
In late January 2025, Özcan was recalled to Borussia Dortmund following the long-term injury of [[Felix Nmecha]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2025/1/28/BVB-holt-Salih-Oezcan-zurueck.html |title=BVB holt Salih Özcan zurück |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |date=28 January 2025 }}</ref> In March 2026, the club announced that his contract, which was due to expire at the end of the season, would not be renewed.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pinnow |first=Kevin |url=https://www.ruhrnachrichten.de/bvb/bvb-umbruch-lars-ricken-bestaetigt-aus-salih-oezcan-niklas-suele-kader-zukunft-w1166478-2002002245/ |title=Exklusiv: Ricken bestätigt BVB-Aus für Özcan und Süle Dortmund bastelt am Kader der Zukunft |publisher=Ruhr Nachrichten |language=de |date=13 March 2026 }}</ref> He left the club at the end of the 2025–26 season, with his final game being on May 8 in a 3–2 win over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] where he came off the bench in the 78th minute for [[Marcel Sabitzer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/747008/eintracht-frankfurt-borussia-dortmund|title=Dortmund 3-2 Frankfurt (May 8, 2026) Final Score - ESPN|date=May 8, 2026|work=[[ESPN]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Özcan was eligible for both the [[Turkey national football team|Turkish]] and [[Germany national football team|German]] national teams,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.express.de/sport/fussball/1--fc-koeln/mavraj---oezcan-das-geheimnis-einer-besonderen-fc-freundschaft-25192618-seite3 |title=1. FC Köln: Mergim Mavraj und Salih Özcan sprechen über ihre Freundschaft &#124; Express.de |access-date=5 February 2017 |archive-date=11 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111074358/http://www.express.de/sport/fussball/1--fc-koeln/mavraj---oezcan-das-geheimnis-einer-besonderen-fc-freundschaft-25192618-seite3 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and played for Germany's youth teams.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/datencenter/personen/salih-oezcan/spieler|title=Salih Özcan – Spielerprofil|website=DFB Datencenter}}</ref> He played his last game for [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]] on 6 June 2021, starting in the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship final|UEFA European Under-21 Championship final]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Germany U21 1-0 Portugal U21 (Jun 6, 2021) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/590548 |access-date=2024-10-24 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

On 25 March 2022, Özcan was called up to the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] by head coach [[Stefan Kuntz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=37316|title=Salih Özcan aday kadroya dâhil edildi|website=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|language=tr}}</ref> He debuted in a friendly 3–2 loss to [[Italy national football team|Italy]] on 29 March 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/03/29/world/friendlies/turkey/italy/3764998/|title = Turkey vs. Italy – 29 March 2022 – Soccerway}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, he was named in the final squad of 26 players selected by [[Vincenzo Montella]] to take part in [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-06-13 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Kadrosu Açıklandı - A Milli Takım Haber Detayları TFF |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |website=www.tff.org}}</ref> On 18 November 2025, he scored his first national goal against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref name="tffgoal">{{Cite web |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=49064 |title=Bileti Mart'ta Alacağız, Teşekkürler Bizim Çocuklar! İSPANYA 2-2 TÜRKİYE |website=TFF.org |access-date=18 November 2025 |date=18 November 2025 |language=tr}}</ref>

